WEBVTT

00:06.440 --> 00:10.149
<i>In my four years, there have been</i>
<i>many emergencies at Sacred Heart,</i>

00:10.240 --> 00:12.674
<i>but none like this one, because today...</i>

00:12.760 --> 00:15.320
Where is he?

00:16.360 --> 00:19.591
<i>Dr Cox's son needed two stitches.</i>

00:20.120 --> 00:22.315
- I got here as soon...
- Shut it, Newbie.

00:22.400 --> 00:24.391
Your blacker half is concentrating.

00:24.480 --> 00:28.029
- How are you holding up?
- I'm a little nervous.

00:28.120 --> 00:30.111
Well, now you make me all nervous.

00:30.200 --> 00:33.954
I'd focus, because that tiny patch
of skin on my son's forehead

00:34.040 --> 00:36.474
is more important to me
than then entirety

00:36.560 --> 00:38.710
of your high-fiving, head-shaving,

00:38.800 --> 00:41.678
air-balling,
insulin-needing existence,

00:41.760 --> 00:45.958
which I guarantee will come
to an abrupt, very unnatural end.

00:47.320 --> 00:48.514
OK, I'm done.

00:48.600 --> 00:50.431
<i>We all held our breath together.</i>

00:52.880 --> 00:54.552
The surgeon lives!

00:58.000 --> 01:00.560
The Todd forgot to breathe again.

01:00.640 --> 01:02.870
Starting CPR.

01:04.400 --> 01:06.630
Mr Gerst, what seems to be the problem?

01:06.720 --> 01:09.075
- I took some pills.
- Come on, help me out here.

01:09.160 --> 01:12.436
Happy pills, sad pills,
sleeping pills, sane pills, pain pills,

01:12.520 --> 01:14.750
- brain pills, Spain pills...
- Man pills.

01:14.840 --> 01:18.355
The commercial says consult a physician
if the condition persists

01:18.440 --> 01:20.874
- for more than four hours.
- If what persists?

01:26.080 --> 01:28.071
Let's just say you took uppers.

01:31.560 --> 01:34.711
Dude, check out what I found
when I was taking out the trash!

01:36.240 --> 01:38.629
That is the most ridiculous hat
I've ever seen.

01:38.720 --> 01:40.233
<i>And I must have it.</i>

01:40.520 --> 01:42.636
Aren't you gonna be late to meet Carla?

01:42.720 --> 01:43.789
I've got time.

01:43.880 --> 01:47.839
Turk and Carla were having trouble,
so she'd been staying at Elliot's.

01:47.920 --> 01:49.319
You were late the last time.

01:49.400 --> 01:52.198
But I set the clock ahead
an hour so I wouldn't be late.

01:52.280 --> 01:55.590
I set it back three so we could see
what it felt like in Honolulu.

01:55.680 --> 01:58.274
I set it ahead five
so I wouldn't feel like a skeeve

01:58.360 --> 01:59.839
for watching porn in the day.

01:59.920 --> 02:03.549
I set it back to 8.08, turned it upside
down to see if it looked like "Bob",

02:03.640 --> 02:05.551
- which it does...
- That's true.

02:05.640 --> 02:08.393
Which means that it's actually...

02:09.440 --> 02:10.429
- 9.52!
- 9.52!

02:10.520 --> 02:13.239
My God! I gotta be downtown
in, like, eight minutes!

02:13.400 --> 02:15.914
Dude, we're never gonna make it in time!

02:16.000 --> 02:20.039
- Take a shortcut through that hedge!
- You got it, player!

02:20.680 --> 02:22.910
Hold on, buddy!

02:26.800 --> 02:29.997
- That was a thick bush.
- Really, Turk, was it a thick bush?

02:30.080 --> 02:32.958
Because there's berries in my ass.
Just go!

02:35.200 --> 02:37.589
Sorry. My bad, dude. My bad.

