02:47.400 --> 02:49.197
Don't worry, Turk, I got 'em!

02:52.200 --> 02:53.872
<i>Strike!</i>

02:56.400 --> 02:59.039
Turk, why are you wearing pyjamas?

02:59.120 --> 03:01.031
I really want you to come home,

03:01.120 --> 03:04.157
and on the off chance you said yes,
I'd be ready to snuggle,

03:04.240 --> 03:07.437
and that would hopefully lead to,
but necessarily require,

03:07.520 --> 03:10.432
relations of the intimate nature.

03:10.520 --> 03:14.911
Turk, with everything that's happened,
I'm just having trouble trusting you.

03:15.000 --> 03:17.912
If there's anyone in this world
you can trust, it's me.

03:18.000 --> 03:21.470
Turk, you're the one I don't know
if I can trust, so how am I supposed

03:21.560 --> 03:24.711
to trust that I can trust you telling me
that I can trust you?

03:24.800 --> 03:27.439
My head hurts.

03:28.080 --> 03:30.275
I wish I knew how it was going.

03:30.920 --> 03:35.118
Sorry about your hogs, fellas.
Enjoy the free espressos.

03:37.880 --> 03:39.836
Warlord, I told you to sip it.

03:41.440 --> 03:44.796
- Use your words.
- Warlord burn mouth.

03:44.880 --> 03:46.552
He did, cos he wasn't listening.

03:46.640 --> 03:49.518
Napkin on your lap, Satan's Valet.
Thank you.

04:07.640 --> 04:10.598
Hey, what are you doing, Frankenstein?

04:10.680 --> 04:12.875
Photo journal for my photography class.

04:12.960 --> 04:15.554
Terrific. Could I see your camera?

04:15.640 --> 04:18.313
Very interesting.
Oh, there's film in it.

04:19.640 --> 04:22.108
Hey! All my pictures were in there!

04:22.200 --> 04:25.158
"Dead Patient With Shirt",
"Dead Patient Without Shirt",

04:25.240 --> 04:27.629
"Me in Shirt Being Yelled
at by Angry Family".

04:27.720 --> 04:29.915
Do you have any idea
of what would unfold

04:30.000 --> 04:31.956
if Jordan were to see that picture?

04:32.040 --> 04:35.919
It is a heart-wrenching tale of woe
involving Jordan's second cousin,

04:36.000 --> 04:37.991
who plays for the New England Patriots,

04:38.080 --> 04:41.072
and me having a Super Bowl ring
removed from my oesophagus.

04:41.160 --> 04:43.594
Jordan's never going
to see these stitches.

04:43.680 --> 04:45.671
Well, I hope you realise this means war.

04:45.760 --> 04:47.751
Buzz off, you big monkey.

04:50.240 --> 04:51.514
Poor Mr Gerst.

04:51.600 --> 04:54.353
What's that like,
to have an erection for nine hours.

04:54.440 --> 04:56.032
Ask me in 20 minutes.

04:56.120 --> 05:00.910
Get this. He doesn't have erectile
dysfunction. Why take those drugs?

05:01.000 --> 05:02.194
What's this?

05:02.280 --> 05:05.397
Why, it's a dummygram,
and it's addressed to you, Barbie.

05:05.480 --> 05:09.109
Let's read it and find out what's
in there. You are disturbingly naive.

05:09.200 --> 05:13.876
Stop. Almost 50 percent of ED drugs
are taken by recreational users.

05:13.960 --> 05:16.235
- Stop.
- That can't be true.

05:17.120 --> 05:20.271
Everyone, would you go ahead
and close your eyes for a second?

05:20.360 --> 05:24.148
Great. Now, would all the men in the
room who have tried Mr Happy pills

05:24.240 --> 05:27.277
go ahead and grab your fork
and bang your glass.

05:31.200 --> 05:32.713
Thank you.

05:35.040 --> 05:36.632
Ted, everyone stopped!

05:37.600 --> 05:40.034
Oh, damn it!

05:42.320 --> 05:45.517
- She's got this trust issue.
- Just tell her she can trust you.

05:45.600 --> 05:48.273
I did. If I'm the one
she didn't know she could trust,

05:48.360 --> 05:51.079
how is she supposed to trust me
telling her she can?

05:51.160 --> 05:52.878
- My head hurts.
- Mine did too.

05:52.960 --> 05:54.518
- I need you to go in.
- No way.

05:54.600 --> 05:57.751
It's never smart to get
in the middle of a relationship.

05:57.840 --> 05:59.319
I'll let you wear my top hat.

05:59.400 --> 06:01.960
Hey! Want to grab a beer?

06:02.040 --> 06:03.598
Lose the hat.

06:06.640 --> 06:08.471
- Hi.
- Hello, there.

06:08.560 --> 06:10.232
What's with all the Band-Aids?

06:10.320 --> 06:14.711
Jack was getting nutty, having some fun.
See, I even let him put one on me.

06:14.800 --> 06:16.756
- Really?
- Yeah.

06:19.000 --> 06:22.197
- Are those stitches?
- What are the odds you'd pick that one?

06:22.280 --> 06:24.748
Jack just...
He just fell off of the jungle gym.

06:24.840 --> 06:26.558
You're not careful enough!

06:26.640 --> 06:29.154
What about the time he brained himself?

06:29.240 --> 06:31.356
- That was an accident.
- Quick question.

06:31.440 --> 06:33.431
Why is it an accident
when he's with you,

06:33.520 --> 06:36.432
but when Jack gets hurt on my time,
I'm not careful enough?

06:36.520 --> 06:38.511
Because I...

06:39.600 --> 06:41.875
Oh, dear God.

06:41.960 --> 06:43.871
You're speechless.

06:43.960 --> 06:48.476
I won! I won an argument.
Jack, it's unprecedented.

06:48.560 --> 06:52.269
We'll be at the playground
drinking beer. Oh, God, we love beer!

06:52.360 --> 06:53.839
But...

06:56.920 --> 07:00.037
That guy needs to do some
serious thinking about baseball.

07:00.120 --> 07:02.429
- He wouldn't even let me see it.
- Meathead.

07:03.360 --> 07:04.679
Good, you both looked.

07:04.760 --> 07:07.479
Now, Mr Gerst came here for help,
and we're doctors,

07:07.560 --> 07:11.109
so how about we try and treat him
with a bit of dignity and respect?

07:12.520 --> 07:15.273
That man is a human sundial.

07:20.160 --> 07:23.311
It's so nice to get out.

07:24.200 --> 07:25.792
Do you know who sings the song?

07:25.880 --> 07:28.155
I can tell you who doesn't:
Billy Joel,

07:28.240 --> 07:31.038
who brought us hits
as <i>Uptown Girl</i> and <i>Matter of Trust.</i>

07:31.120 --> 07:34.032
Speaking of trust,
you know who's trustworthy? Turk.

07:34.120 --> 07:38.193
I call him Turkey-Turkey-Turkey-
Turkey-Trust-Trust. A little nickname.

07:38.280 --> 07:41.352
J.D., I know what you're
trying to do and it's very sweet,

07:41.440 --> 07:44.796
but the last couple of days have
been so messed up and confusing,

07:44.880 --> 07:48.077
I'd love to just try and forget about it
and have a few drinks, OK?

07:48.160 --> 07:50.594
I'd talk about him
until you made me leave.

07:50.680 --> 07:54.116
- I'll let you put the hat back on.
- Two appletinis, governor.

07:57.160 --> 07:59.754
Look at my girl.
Right back up on the monkey bars,

07:59.840 --> 08:02.149
after she chipped
her tooth there last week.

08:02.240 --> 08:06.518
My kid's got a forehead full of stitches
from leaping off the jungle gym.

08:06.600 --> 08:09.558
When my wife's not around,
I let her stand on my shoulders.

08:09.640 --> 08:12.154
Really? Wait till you
get a load of this.

08:12.520 --> 08:16.354
OK, here we go. What are we doing?
Come here, you. You come here, you.

08:18.440 --> 08:21.113
Giant man,
why are you making that noise?

08:21.200 --> 08:23.555
Because my camera
doesn't make a real sound,

08:23.640 --> 08:26.473
and it's more fun that way.
See? You go...

08:28.600 --> 08:30.989
Look happy. Look sad.

08:32.120 --> 08:34.111
Look crazy.

08:34.200 --> 08:35.712
Look like you're going away.

08:40.120 --> 08:42.554
You need to set
an example of professionalism.

08:42.640 --> 08:45.950
You're not gonna do that
by making fun of that man's slinky-doo.

08:46.040 --> 08:50.272
Don't pull me!
I'm your boss, for God's... Hello!

08:50.360 --> 08:54.069
Well, Mr Gerst, your situation
doesn't seem to be reversing itself,

08:54.160 --> 08:57.789
so I think we're gonna need to
schedule a procedure to relieve the...

09:00.160 --> 09:02.355
Woodiness.

09:02.440 --> 09:06.035
