wanted to do something special.

09:06.120 --> 09:09.396
Turns out she just meant
having breakfast with her family.

09:09.480 --> 09:12.438
Those pills didn't kick in
until just about the moment

09:12.520 --> 09:14.988
I'm introduced to her
90-year-old grandmother.

09:15.080 --> 09:20.108
And sure enough, that little lady gives
me the waist hug from her wheelchair.

09:20.200 --> 09:21.394
I need that chart.

09:21.480 --> 09:24.233
Sweetheart, it's not healthy
to hold it in. Let it out.

09:24.320 --> 09:26.276
- You know you want to.
- I'm fine.

09:26.360 --> 09:30.990
I pulled away from that encounter with
Grandma Helen's breathing apparatus.

09:34.080 --> 09:36.275
My work here is done.

09:37.520 --> 09:41.877
Oh, my God, I can't stop!
I'm sorry. I have to pee.

09:44.160 --> 09:46.879
OK, J.D., why are we sitting up here?

09:46.960 --> 09:50.953
Because you can see Elliot's
whole apartment from up here.

09:51.040 --> 09:52.758
J.D., you're drunk.

09:52.840 --> 09:56.549
Carla, I'm not as think
as you drunk I am.

09:59.080 --> 10:00.957
Then why can't you let go of the couch?

10:01.040 --> 10:03.679
I can let go of the couch
if I so choose.

10:03.760 --> 10:06.115
OK, let go of the couch. Let it go.

10:08.440 --> 10:09.953
You see?

10:15.840 --> 10:19.594
<i>There are many things we can't control,</i>
<i>no matter how strong we might be...</i>

10:20.720 --> 10:23.075
<i>... like a knee-jerk reaction...</i>

10:23.160 --> 10:26.197
I am so sorry.

10:27.280 --> 10:30.750
I'm done. I'm done. Yes.

10:30.840 --> 10:32.353
It's OK.

10:35.920 --> 10:38.354
<i>... or a janitor who has it in for you.</i>

10:39.360 --> 10:43.194
Hi. Look what someone
was nice enough to give me.

10:46.120 --> 10:47.712
Janitor.

10:53.240 --> 10:56.073
Oh, thank you for helping me
have some fun tonight.

10:56.160 --> 10:58.037
You're welcome.

10:58.120 --> 11:02.159
<i>Sometimes you let go of the control you</i>
<i>do have in a brief moment of weakness.</i>

11:07.440 --> 11:09.874
Sorry. Drunken accident.

11:09.960 --> 11:11.518
- Nothing happened.
- Right.

11:11.600 --> 11:13.192
- Good night.
- Good night.

11:13.280 --> 11:14.998
- Good night.
- Good night.

11:15.080 --> 11:18.470
- <i>Buenas...</i> nose things.
- Good night.

11:20.400 --> 11:22.675
<i>Like she said, everything's fine.</i>

11:27.960 --> 11:30.520
<i>There's nothing like the rays</i>
<i>of the morning sun</i>

11:30.600 --> 11:35.037
<i>reminding you that you got drunk</i>
<i>and kissed your best friend's wife.</i>

11:35.120 --> 11:38.112
- Oh, my God!
- Oh, my God!

11:38.200 --> 11:40.191
- It really happened?
- It was nothing!

11:40.280 --> 11:42.316
- There wasn't tongue!
- No tongue!

11:42.400 --> 11:44.391
- A friend kiss.
- Were your lips parted?

11:44.480 --> 11:46.198
No, I pursed them like this.

11:46.280 --> 11:48.714
I remember my one lip
being on top of your lip,

11:48.800 --> 11:50.870
my other lip in the middle of yours.

11:50.960 --> 11:54.191
Your lips were apart
and I don't think that's a friend kiss!

11:54.280 --> 11:57.113
It's a friend kiss,
and we will never talk about this!

11:57.200 --> 11:59.111
- All right.
- What's going on?

11:59.200 --> 12:00.633
- Nothing.
- We kissed.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.119
- Carla!
- A friend kiss?

12:02.200 --> 12:03.269
- Yes. Carla!
- No!

12:03.360 --> 12:04.793
You're killing me!

12:07.960 --> 12:11.032
- This never leaves the room!
- Why did you close my window?

12:14.760 --> 12:18.548
Oh, no! She wrote "J.D. And Carla
kissed" and she's gonna tell Turk!

12:18.640 --> 12:20.949
No, no, stop her!

12:21.040 --> 12:23.679
Don't worry, ladies,
I've closed the window.

12:29.680 --> 12:32.114
J.D., I don't have a messenger monkey.

12:34.720 --> 12:38.190
All right, fine, I'm a little rougher
than you are, but guess what?

12:38.280 --> 12:41.556
The two of us have two distinctly
different parenting styles.

12:41.640 --> 12:47.317
You're an overbearing psychotic,
and I'm, well, you know... fun.

12:47.400 --> 12:51.632
If we can meet somewhere in the middle,
I think Jack's gonna be terrific.

12:51.720 --> 12:55.190
Besides, it's not like I ever
put him in any real danger.

12:55.600 --> 12:56.715
Flip!

12:56.800 --> 12:59.360
Flip? What does "flip" mean, Perry?

12:59.440 --> 13:03.831
Jack probably thinks that Mommy and
Daddy are being a little too sarcastic.

13:03.920 --> 13:04.989
Maybe.

13:05.080 --> 13:07.548
Or it's because
every time he says "flip",

13:07.640 --> 13:10.950
Daddy does a little trick
where he grabs Jack by the ankles,

13:11.040 --> 13:15.431
he flips him upside down, he drops him
down onto his shoulders and then...

13:15.520 --> 13:17.590
...puts him in a little baby trapeze,

13:17.680 --> 13:20.399
shoots him across
the sand box without a net.

13:21.520 --> 13:24.592
You are never taking Jack
to the park without me. Ever!

13:24.680 --> 13:26.159
Jordan.

13:27.920 --> 13:31.879
- A trapeze?
- Yeah. Photoshop. You can do anything.

13:31.960 --> 13:34.599
Here I have you wearing
a duck's bill. Get it?

13:35.560 --> 13:37.118
Because you're a quack.

13:37.960 --> 13:39.439
No?!

13:39.520 --> 13:42.398
Come on. Classic comedy, my friend.

13:42.480 --> 13:44.311
He'll learn.

13:44.400 --> 13:47.870
I'm a horrible person. There I was,
on my high horse about Mr Gerst,

13:47.960 --> 13:50.269
then I turned out to be as bad
as everyone else.

13:50.360 --> 13:53.557
Give yourself some credit.
You were worse than everyone else.

13:53.640 --> 13:56.916
Maybe I was, but you know what?
I'm gonna try and better myself.

13:57.000 --> 14:00.356
Unlike you, I'll follow through,
Mr Sign Up on the Bulletin Board

14:00.440 --> 14:03.113
for German Lessons
and Never Show Up. That's right.

14:03.200 --> 14:04.599
It was my flier...

14:06.920 --> 14:10.435
I broke up with my German mistress.
She smells like sauerkraut.

14:10.520 --> 14:11.919
I'm so sorry.

14:12.000 --> 14:14.833
If you'll excuse me,
I'm gonna go into that room right now

14:14.920 --> 14:16.797
and own up to what I did.

14:20.280 --> 14:23.875
Hello? Did someone come in?

14:26.760 --> 14:29.228
<i>I had to hide from Turk,</i>
<i>so I went to the one place</i>

14:29.320 --> 14:31.311
<i>where I knew no one would ever venture.</i>

14:31.400 --> 14:34.119
Ted? Ted?

14:34.200 --> 14:36.555
- A little help!
- Ted, what are you doing?

14:36.640 --> 14:39.518
I like to do stomach crunches
after lunch.

14:39.600 --> 14:41.352
Ted, lunch was four hours ago.

14:41.440 --> 14:45.194
- Yep, I wasted most of my Tuesday.
- It's Wednesday.

14:45.280 --> 14:48.590
Oh, man, I missed the <i>Gilmore Girls!</i>

14:51.280 --> 14:53.157
- There you are. Hey, Ted.
- Hey.

14:53.240 --> 14:56.437
- How did it go last night?
- What's with the fifth degree?

14:56.520 --> 14:59.432
- Don't you mean third degree?
- This is two degrees worse.

14:59.520 --> 15:01.988
I can't breathe.
I'm trapped in a death coffin.

15:02.080 --> 15:04.071
I wanted to see if you got anywhere.

15:04.160 --> 15:07.550
<i>He knows your lying face,</i>
<i>but silence is incriminating too. Think!</i>

15:07.640 --> 15:10.279
<i>What's between silence and talking?</i>

15:12.000 --> 15:15.231
Turk? I thought you could
take me over to Elliot's place

15:15.320 --> 15:17.550
to get my stuff so I could move back in.

15:17.640 --> 15:19.915
Yeah, sure... Really?

15:21.400 --> 15:23.675
- All right, meet me downstairs, OK?
- OK.

15:23.760 --> 15:25.591
I owe you one.

15:27.680 --> 15:30.513
You should sit down.
You're looking a little purple.

15:30.600 --> 15:32.477
I know my own body.

15:37.360 --> 15:40.955
- Thanks for saving my ass.
- Well, I wasn't saving your ass.

15:41.040 --> 15:43.838
I didn't realize how easy it is
to make little mistakes.

15:43.920 --> 15:46.559
They're stupid mistakes
that seem like nothing,

15:46.640 --> 15:50.952
but can snowball on you and take
your whole marriage with it, you know?

15:51.040 --> 15:56.797
I feel like I understand now how Turk
could have let stuff like that happen.

15:56.880 --> 15:59.075
So I forgave him.

15:59.160 --> 16:03.119
- Well, I guess I'm glad we kissed then.
- Me too.

16:04.200 --> 16:07.351
- You guys ready?
- Yeah, we are. Let's do it.

16:15.520 --> 16:18.592
OK, we just saw the plastic surgeon.

16:18.680 --> 16:22.878
Jack is fine, but if the cut was four
inches to the left and 7 inches deeper,

16:22.960 --> 16:25.428
it could have
potentially scratched his eye.

16:25.520 --> 16:29.229
- That was a close one.
- What a sweet little angel.

16:29.640 --> 16:31.756
Can I just give him a little squeeze?

16:31.840 --> 16:33.319
Of course.

16:33.400 --> 16:34.674
Back off there, lady.

16:34.760 --> 16:38.230
Save up all that energy for the cruise.
Go on, get out of here.

16:38.320 --> 16:41.073
Hippity-hop to the barber shop.
Come on, Mom.

16:41.160 --> 16:44.391
This hospital is literally
crawling with germs and disease.

16:44.480 --> 16:47.313
In all fairness,
you don't know if that lady is a sickie,

16:47.400 --> 16:50.676
visiting a sickie and she ran
her hands all over his sickie face.

16:50.760 --> 16:53.797
- I normally never let people touch him.
- Really?

16:53.880 --> 16:56.440
Because these photographs
would beg to differ.

16:56.520 --> 17:01.548
Old lady kissing Jack,
teenage girl hugging Jack,

17:01.640 --> 17:04.915
homeless man... holding Jack.

17:05.000 --> 17:07.594
- Jordan!
- It's just Carl.

17:07.680 --> 17:09.590
He holds Jack when I get a bikini wax.

17:09.680 --> 17:13.593
What's the matter with me? I don't
think twice about people holding him,

17:13.680 --> 17:17.150
yet I obsess about things
like broken arms, broken legs, choking,

17:17.240 --> 17:20.516
kidnapping, drowning,
bad babysitters, pretty babysitters.

17:20.599 --> 17:23.239
I freak out over staph infections,
blood disease,

17:23.319 --> 17:25.550
mumps, measles,
sex, drugs, rock and roll

17:25.640 --> 17:29.315
and all registered Independents.
Between us, we've got it covered.

17:29.400 --> 17:32.870
- Was this taken at my mother's house?
- I gotta go.

17:34.640 --> 17:37.108
Dude, that did not happen.

17:37.200 --> 17:41.352
No, I'm in the hospital because I...
They think I have avian flu.

17:42.520 --> 17:45.353
I gotta call you back.
How long have you been there?

17:45.440 --> 17:50.594
Oh, 47, 48 minutes. I'm not sure.
I nodded off for a while.

17:50.680 --> 17:54.036
Mr Gerst, I'm so sorry
for laughing at you.

17:54.120 --> 17:56.588
I have to tell a story.
In the seventh grade,

17:56.680 --> 17:59.558
I was at a roller rink
and I needed to go to the bathroom.

17:59.640 --> 18:03.155
So I just skated right on into a stall
and I did my private business.

18:03.240 --> 18:04.753
When I went to pull up my pants,

18:04.840 --> 18:07.832
I started rolling towards the door,
which wasn't latched.

18:07.920 --> 18:11.833
I don't know if you've had experience
skating with underpants at your ankles.

18:11.920 --> 18:14.309
Difficult to stop.
Unless, you scream so loud

18:14.400 --> 18:16.994
they turn off the music
and everyone looks at you.

18:17.080 --> 18:20.390
Anyway, that's how I wound up
with the nickname Roller Moler.

18:20.480 --> 18:23.313
- I'm sorry?
- I have a mole on my ass.

18:23.400 --> 18:25.994
The cute kind, not the hairy kind.

18:26.080 --> 18:28.878
The next day I showed up at school
with roller skates on,

18:28.960 --> 18:31.952
- and everybody cracked up.
- Why are you telling me this?

18:32.040 --> 18:35.157
Because I owned up to it.
This is funny, Mr Gerst.

18:35.240 --> 18:39.916
If you don't become part of the joke,
it will follow and devour you.

18:40.000 --> 18:43.709
- Can I get a look at that mole?
- No. No.

18:46.400 --> 18:50.552
This is nice, the three of us sitting
together again like three musketeers.

18:50.640 --> 18:53.438
Yeah. And I need you guys
to scrape your plates

18:53.520 --> 18:56.034
before you put them in the dishwasher.

18:56.120 --> 18:59.271
She's back. My baby's back!

19:01.360 --> 19:05.194
<i>Carla was right. If a relationship's</i>
<i>gonna work, it has to be based on trust,</i>

19:05.280 --> 19:07.919
<i>like a wife trusting her husband.</i>

19:08.480 --> 19:10.436
- Kid's back on the jungle gym.
- Sure.

19:10.520 --> 19:13.592
- Guess your wife backed down.
- Bet your sweet ass she did.

19:13.680 --> 19:15.716
<i>Even if it involves a compromise.</i>

19:17.240 --> 19:20.038
Hey, Jack! Just blink
when you want me to get you down.

19:20.120 --> 19:22.998
Just give me the old blink-a-roonie.
Terrific athlete.

19:23.080 --> 19:25.469
I'm thinking 2016 Olympics.

19:25.560 --> 19:27.710
Oh, God, was that a blink?
Excuse me.

19:30.440 --> 19:33.989
<i>Or a patient trusting his doctor</i>
<i>to help him hold on to his dignity.</i>

19:34.080 --> 19:37.436
Yes, and then I pulled off
Grandma's breathing apparatus.

19:37.520 --> 19:39.556
No, I'm serious.

19:40.240 --> 19:42.629
<i>It may take a lot of work,</i>
<i>but it's worth it.</i>

19:44.920 --> 19:48.196
Wow, that was a moist kiss.
Wish I was wearing an apron.

19:48.280 --> 19:52.193
Baby, from here on out,
I hide nothing from you.

19:52.280 --> 19:53.952
It's a clean start for us.

19:55.480 --> 19:56.879
Sports time!

19:56.960 --> 19:59.952
<i>Because in the end,</i>
<i>things work out for the best.</i>

20:01.200 --> 20:03.350
J.D. And I kissed.

20:07.680 --> 20:09.352
<i>Or not.</i>

